A lightweight, high-performance event tracking pipeline built using Node.js, Redis, and MongoDB.
Supports fast event ingestion, background processing, and real-time daily analytics.


Client → Ingestion API → Redis Queue → Worker → MongoDB → Reporting API

Ingestion Service: Validates events & pushes them to Redis instantly.

Worker: Consumes queue events, stores raw data, and updates daily aggregates.

Reporting API: Returns total views, unique users, and top paths for a site.

------------- Tech Stack

Node.js (Express)

Redis (queue + unique user sets)

MongoDB (events + daily_aggregates)

Joi (validation)

------------- Project Structure
analytics-project/
├── ingestion/
├── processor/
├── reporting/
└── README.md

-------------- Running the System (Local)
Start Redis
brew services start redis

Start MongoDB
brew services start mongodb-community@7.0

Start Services

Run each in separate terminals:

Ingestion

cd ingestion
npm start


Worker

cd processor
npm start


Reporting

cd reporting
npm start

------------Testing
Send Event
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/event \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"site_id":"site-1","event_type":"page_view","path":"/home","user_id":"u1","timestamp":"2025-11-12T12:00:00Z"}'

Get Stats
curl "http://localhost:3001/stats?site_id=site-1&date=2025-11-12"

--------- Output Example
{
  "site_id": "site-1",
  "date": "2025-11-12",
  "total_views": 10,
  "unique_users": 5,
  "top_paths": [
    { "path": "/home", "views": 7 }
  ]
}

----------- Features

Fast ingestion (non-blocking)

Asynchronous processing via Redis queue

Daily aggregates

Unique users via Redis sets

Graceful shutdown

Health endpoints

------------- Future Improvements

HyperLogLog for uniques

Kafka/SQS for queueing

Dashboard UI